#Commands to setup monitor mode in command prompt:
<!-- Monitor Mode was enabled using the following commands:
This command terminates interfering network processes to allow Monitor Mode activation: -->
sudo airmon-ng check kill
<!-- This converts the wireless interface (wlp0s20f3) into Monitor Mode: -->
sudo airmon-ng start wlp0s20f3
<!-- Note: wlp0s20f3 is the Linux system name for the wireless network interface card (NIC), assigned dynamically by the operating system. -->
<!-- After activation, the interface typically appears as:
Wlp0s20f3mon
Disabling Monitor Mode -->
sudo airmon-ng stop wlp0s20f3mon
